19
TA to State Teams
Designed for 4-6 state teams interested in developing a state process 
Teams will receive support from subject matter experts and project
advisors and engage in peer learning and sharing opportunities 
20
TA Objectives
TA will help state teams achieve the following objectives:
• Increase their knowledge of the state process option, the
application process, and related requirements 
• Explore examples of currently approved state processes 
• Determine state priorities, processes, and requirements for a
state-defined process 
• Develop a state process that builds and leverages (1) intentional
and sustained systems, (2) clear and collaborative partnerships,
and (3) a learner-centered mindset 
21
State Team Composition
• Adult Education State Director (or designee)
• Career and Technical Education (CTE) State Director (or designee)
• Director of state’s community and technical college system (or
designee)
• State agency staff member who has responsibility and/or knowledge
of federal student aid (or designee)
• Representatives from 1-2 community or technical college(s) with
ATB experience (e g , director of financial aid and directors of adult
education/career pathway initiatives)
22
