Application Components
• Name and contact information for state agencies and participating
staff, which should include at minimum:
• Adult Education State Director (or designee)
• Career and Technical Education (CTE) State Director (or designee)
• Director of state’s community and technical college system (or designee)
• State agency staff member who has responsibility and/or knowledge of
federal student aid (or designee)
• Names of 1-2 two-year public community and technical colleges with
ATB experience -- include names, titles, and contact information for
relevant staff
• Names, titles, and contact information for any additional team
members the state would like to include
30
Application Components (continued)
• Letters of support from community or technical colleges’ president
or vice president
• Applicants will be evaluated by the project team staff on their
responses to the application:
• Goals for expanding ATB that are aligned with other state priorities
• Prior experience and/or demonstrated interest and commitment to ATB
• The name(s) of at least one public institution in the state that has already
implemented ATB usage or is in the process of designing programs for ATB
• Experience building and leveraging cross-sector, multi-stakeholder
partnerships for career pathways initiatives
